KernelCheck 1.1.4

About KernelCheck
=================
KernelCheck is a project that is designed to easily build the latest kernel for your distribution using the instructions provided in the Master Kernel Thread. This automated process is a fork of AutoKernel by Robert Wolterman (xtacocorex), Timothy Janssen (mentok), and Kristof Verbeken (PingunZ). KernelCheck is currently stable and ready for public use.

Requirements (most systems come with these by default)
============
PyGTK 2.0
Zenity

Basic Installation
==================

1. Uncompress the archive - Console command:
	tar -xzf kernelcheck-$version.tar.gz

2. Change to the uncompressed directory - Console command:
	cd kernelcheck-$version

3. Run setup.py to install the program - Console command:
	sudo python setup.py install

4. Run the program by typing 'kernelcheck' - Console command:
	kernelcheck

